    "IND_SIM": {
      "name": "Similarity",
      "definition": "IND_SIM quantifies the uniformity and repetition of visual elements within a given environment. It assesses the extent to which textures, colors, forms, or architectural styles are replicated across a scene. While high similarity contributes to a sense of order and harmony, excessive similarity can lead to monotony. In urban design analysis, this indicator helps evaluate the balance between chaotic diversity and cohesive identity, ensuring that a streetscape possesses enough unifying traits to be aesthetically pleasing without becoming tedious.",
