    "IND_SHA": {
      "name": "Shade Coverage",
      "definition": "IND_SHA calculates the proportion of a specific area or visual frame that is protected from direct solar radiation by obstructions such as trees, buildings, or canopies. This indicator is a vital component of thermal comfort modelling and microclimate analysis. By quantifying the extent of shadowed surfaces, planners can assess the usability of outdoor spaces during hot periods. It links the physical configuration of urban geometry and vegetation canopy to the physiological well-being and cooling experience of pedestrians.",
