    "SRC_FLD": {
      "name": "Field Survey",
      "definition": "SRC_FLD involves the direct observation and collection of data within the actual physical environment rather than through remote sensing or simulations. This method encompasses on-site measurements, photography, observation of user behavior, and physical audits of site conditions. Field surveys provide ground-truth data that captures the nuances of the genius loci, sensory inputs (sound, smell), and ephemeral conditions that laboratory or digital analyses might miss. It ensures the validity of the dataset by verifying real-world conditions against theoretical models.",
