      "definition": "SRC_PAN refers to 360-degree panoramic imagery, typically captured using omnidirectional cameras or by stitching together multiple images. These wide-angle visual representations provide a comprehensive, immersive view of a physical environment, allowing for the assessment of urban streetscapes and environmental features from a user-centric perspective. In computational analysis, these images are often projected into equirectangular formats to facilitate semantic segmentation and feature extraction.",
