      "definition": "UNT_MTR signifies the meter, the fundamental unit of length in the International System of Units (SI). In geospatial and urban studies, it serves as the primary metric for defining distances, heights, and spatial resolutions. Whether measuring the width of street canyons, the height of buildings, or the distance between amenities, quantifying these dimensions in meters ensures consistency and compatibility with global cartographic standards and spatial databases.",
