    "UNT_UGM3": {
      "name": "Micrograms per Cubic Meter",
      "definition": "A unit of concentration primarily used in environmental science and air quality monitoring to measure the mass of a substance (in micrograms) present within one cubic meter of air. It is the standard metric for quantifying the levels of particulate matter (such as PM2.5 and PM10) and various gaseous pollutants to assess compliance with health standards and environmental regulations.",
