    "REL_MED": {
      "name": "Mediation",
      "definition": "REL_MED identifies a mechanism through which an independent variable influences a dependent variable, explaining the 'how' or 'why' of a relationship. In a mediation model, the intervention or exposure affects a mediator variable, which in turn affects the outcome. This analysis is crucial for understanding causal pathways, such as how green space (independent variable) reduces stress (outcome) specifically through the mechanism of noise reduction (mediator), rather than through a direct, unexplained link.",
