    "REL_MOD": {
      "name": "Moderation",
      "definition": "REL_MOD describes a relationship where a third variable affects the strength or direction of the association between an independent and a dependent variable. A moderator specifies 'when' or 'for whom' an effect occurs. For example, the benefit of a park on mental health might be moderated by age, meaning the relationship changes depending on the demographic group. This analysis highlights interaction effects, revealing boundary conditions and nuances in how environmental factors impact different populations.",
