    "REL_THR": {
      "name": "Threshold",
      "definition": "REL_THR identifies a non-linear relationship where an effect only manifests, accelerates, or ceases once a specific level of the independent variable is reached. This 'tipping point' suggests that below or above a certain concentration or quantity of an environmental factor (such as noise decibels or green space density), the outcome remains stable, but crossing the threshold triggers a distinct change. Understanding these critical points is vital for establishing minimum standards or maximum limits in policy.",
      "category": "CAT_REL",
      "supporting_papers": [
        {
