      "definition": "Analysis of Variance (ANOVA) is a statistical technique used to compare the means of three or more independent groups to determine if at least one group mean is statistically different from the others. By partitioning the total observed variance into variation between groups and variation within groups, ANOVA produces an F-statistic to test the null hypothesis of equal means. It is widely used in experimental designs to analyze the impact of categorical independent variables (factors) on a continuous dependent variable.",
