    "TST_SEM": {
      "name": "Structural Equation Modeling",
      "definition": "Structural Equation Modeling (SEM) is a comprehensive multivariate statistical analysis technique that combines factor analysis and multiple regression. It allows researchers to test complex theoretical models involving both observable and latent (unobservable) variables. SEM explicitly accounts for measurement error and examines structural relationships between variables simultaneously. This approach is particularly useful for theory confirmation, assessing mediation effects, and analyzing complex causal networks where variables can act as both predictors and outcomes within a unified model structure.",
