    "SPU_TRJ": {
      "name": "Trajectory",
      "definition": "A sampling unit representing the continuous path or sequence of positions moved by an object or person over time. Trajectory analysis focuses on the geometric and temporal properties of movement, such as speed, direction, duration, and tortuosity. Often derived from GPS or mobile tracking data, this unit allows researchers to study mobility patterns, exposure to environmental factors along a route, and travel behaviors. It shifts the focus from static locations to dynamic movement, capturing the experience of space as it is traversed.",
