    "SET_HWY": {
      "name": "Highway",
      "definition": "A major high-speed public road designed for heavy vehicular traffic, typically connecting major urban centers or regions. In environmental settings, this designation characterizes areas dominated by infrastructure for rapid transit, often associated with high noise levels, limited pedestrian access, and distinct ecological fragmentation. It represents a utilitarian landscape focused on efficiency of transport rather than social habitation.",
