    "SET_RIV": {
      "name": "River",
      "definition": "A natural flowing watercourse, usually freshwater, flowing towards an ocean, sea, lake, or another river. In urban landscape settings, this category refers to the riparian zone and the immediate water body, often serving as a critical ecological corridor, a recreational amenity, or a hydrological resource. It introduces dynamic natural elements and blue space benefits into the static built environment.",
