    "SET_PUB_HSG": {
      "name": "Public Housing",
      "definition": "Residential developments owned, managed, or subsidized by the government to provide affordable accommodation for low-to-moderate-income households. Morphologically, these settings often feature distinct architectural typologies, such as high-rise blocks or planned estates, with shared communal spaces designed to support specific demographic density and social welfare objectives. They represent a specific intersection of social policy and urban design.",
