    "SET_POS": {
      "name": "Public Open Space",
      "definition": "Accessible outdoor areas within the urban environment that are freely open to the public, including plazas, squares, parks, and waterfronts. These settings are crucial for social interaction, civic engagement, and community health. They are defined by their accessibility and lack of structural enclosure compared to private or indoor environments, acting as the 'living room' of the city.",
