    "SET_PUB_HOU": {
      "name": "Public Housing",
      "definition": "State-subsidized housing estates designed to provide shelter for citizens with financial needs. In the context of environmental analysis, this setting focuses on the specific spatial arrangement of mass housing, often characterized by repetitive building forms, defined semi-public boundaries, and specific community dynamics that differ from private residential subdivisions or mixed-use commercial zones.",
