      "definition": "Recently developed zones typically located on the periphery of existing cities or as part of planned urban expansion projects. These settings are characterized by modern planning principles, contemporary architecture, updated infrastructure networks, and often lower density or distinct zoning separation compared to the organic, historical growth patterns found in older city centers.",
