    "SET_COU": {
      "name": "Courtyard",
      "definition": "An unroofed area that is completely or partially enclosed by walls or buildings. In architectural and urban settings, this space serves as a semi-private or private transitional zone that provides light, ventilation, and a protected area for social interaction. It creates a micro-environment distinct from the fully public street or the fully interior domestic space, often fostering a sense of community among surrounding occupants.",
