      "name": "Deciduous Tree",
      "definition": "Refers to broad-leaved tree species that exhibit a seasonal abscission cycle, shedding their foliage annually, typically at the onset of the dormant season or dry period. Morphologically, these trees provide substantial canopy density during the growing season, offering shade and evapotranspiration benefits, while allowing solar penetration and passive heating during leafless periods. In landscape management, this subtype is characterized by distinct maintenance requirements related to leaf litter management in autumn and structural pruning, which is optimally performed during the winter dormancy phase.",
