      "name": "Oceanic (Cfb)",
      "definition": "Under the Köppen climate classification, the Cfb designation represents an Oceanic climate. It is characterized by temperate weather patterns featuring warm, but not hot, summers where the average temperature of the warmest month remains below 22°C. Winters are generally mild, rarely experiencing extreme freezing conditions for extended periods. Precipitation is dispersed relatively evenly throughout the year without a distinct dry season. This climate is typically found on the western sides of continents at middle latitudes, where maritime air masses heavily influence and moderate temperature extremes.",
