    "KPN_DFA": {
      "name": "Hot-summer Humid Continental (Dfa)",
      "definition": "The Dfa classification signifies a Hot-summer Humid Continental climate. This zone experiences distinct seasonal variations with hot summers, where the average temperature in the warmest month exceeds 22°C, and cold winters with average temperatures dropping significantly below freezing. Precipitation is generally well-distributed year-round, though some locations may see a summer peak. Common in the interior regions of continents in the Northern Hemisphere, this climate poses specific challenges for urban planning, requiring energy-intensive cooling in summer and substantial heating infrastructure during the harsh winter months.",
