    "LCZ_2": {
      "name": "LCZ 2 - Compact Mid-rise",
      "definition": "Local Climate Zone 2 is defined by a dense mix of mid-rise structures, generally ranging from three to nine stories in height. Buildings are closely spaced, resulting in limited sky visibility and moderate-to-high canyon geometries. The land cover is dominated by impervious surfaces such as stone, brick, tile, and concrete, with few or no trees present. The thermal behavior of this zone involves significant heat storage during the day and slow release at night, contributing noticeably to the urban heat island effect, though typically with slightly less intensity than high-rise compact zones.",
