      "name": "LCZ 4 - Open High-rise",
      "definition": "Local Climate Zone 4 is characterized by an open arrangement of tall buildings, generally exceeding ten stories. Unlike compact zones, the buildings here are set significantly apart, allowing for ample airflow and sky visibility. The space between the structures is dominated by low plants, scattered trees, or grass, rather than continuous pavement. This configuration typically creates a cooler microclimate compared to compact zones because the vegetation aids in evapotranspiration and the spacing prevents heat trapping, although the tall structures can still influence wind patterns and cast significant shadows.",
