    "LCZ_A": {
      "name": "LCZ A - Dense Trees",
      "definition": "Local Climate Zone A describes a natural environment heavily populated with deciduous or coniferous trees. The distinguishing feature is a continuous or near-continuous canopy that significantly obstructs the view of the sky and shades the ground. The surface layer consists of permeable soil, leaf litter, or low herbaceous plants. This zone provides maximum evapotranspirative cooling and shading, maintaining lower surface and air temperatures compared to built environments. It includes forests, dense woodlots, or mature urban parks where the density of trees dominates the land cover.",
      "supporting_papers": [
