      "definition": "Incidence Rate Ratio (IRR) is the exponentiated coefficient from a count model with a log link (e.g., Poisson or negative binomial regression). It expresses the multiplicative change in the expected incidence/count for a one-unit increase in the predictor (IRR = exp(β)). IRR < 1 indicates a decrease; IRR > 1 indicates an increase.",
      "recommended_unit_id": "UNT_RTO",
      "recommended_unit": "IRR",
      "definition_source": "project_patch",
